Interface ReturnObject

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ReturnObjectImpl

    public interface ReturnObject
    A wrapper containing either an object (the result of an operation on a data structure) or an error value.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ErrorMessage getError()
      Returns the error message.

    • Method Detail

      • hasError

        boolean hasError()
        Returns whether there has been an error
        Returns:
        whether there has been an error

      • getError

        ErrorMessage getError()
        Returns the error message. This method must return NO_ERROR if and only if returns false.
        Returns:
        the error message

      • getReturnValue

        java.lang.Object getReturnValue()
        Returns the object wrapped in this ReturnObject, i.e. the result of the operation if it was successful, or null if there has been error. Note that the output of this method must be null if hasError returns true, but the opposite is not true: if hasError returns false, this method may or may not return null.
        Returns:
        the return value from the method or null if there has been an error
